From:         Frisco Del Rosario <Frisco_Del_Rosario@CATTEKIN.VIP.BEST.COM>
Subject:      Joan/misc. saturation :)

I'm starting to look at the Joan of Arc/misc.for-sale discussion in the
same fashion I watched stories like the O.J. saga. I mean, at first they're
important and vital, and then they drag on and on, though you're sure it's
a foregone conclusion (guilty as hell), so you stop reading, but it's
always there, and it never goes away, until the jury passes down the wrong
verdict just so they can be done with it, too. (I'm sure Wizards will do
the right thing in this case, however. :)  )

The Joan/Misc. combination has even achieved that rarified illicitness that
belongs to hacker programs like AOHell. Read alt.aol-sucks, for instance,
and little kids post "duh, what is AOHell and how can I get it?" or "duh,
here's what I did with AOHell." Similarly, in trading.cards-misc and this
listserv, little kids post "I've heard so much about Joan and Misc -- what
is it and how can I get it?" or "here's what I did with Joan..."

It occurred to me today that my hope that the card combination will be
fixed in time for Pacificon is foolish, and that I might have to face
nothing but runners playing with Joan and misc. Ugh, how boring.

The fix I see repeatedly is that programs have to hit the trash in order
for misc.for-sale to pay off. I am sure that you clever Joan/misc players
will comply, making sure that no important programs are installed in your
Imp pyramids. :)

In other news, I liked that question where someone asked, "which cards
would you never play with?"

Um, Codeslinger, Record Reconstructor, Japanese Water Torture.

Frisky
"I have asked my French major roommate for something cool to put here"
