when he rolled a Playful AI sequence about 50 times before finally emerging
with a dozen bits. Then he used the bits to run a subsidiary fort that had
a Vacuum Link on it, and I rolled a couple of small numbers myself, sending
him back behind a wall a couple of times.

Hmm ... for Pacificon, I think I'll take a dozen Playful AIs, and hope a
few of them tie up my games as runner long enough for time to be called. :)
