'Ello folks.

Frisco wrote:

> In other news, I liked that question where someone asked, "which cards
> would you never play with?"
>
> Um, Codeslinger, Record Reconstructor, Japanese Water Torture.

Really?  Record Reconstructor I can understand (receives my vote for
most worthless card in the game, and I have 4 of the stupid things!) but
the other two can be very deadly.  My one and only Clown deck used JWT
and Codeslinger and Tinweasel.  4 Zetatech Installers, a few Tycho
Mem Chips and bunches of Clowns later, I only had to pay 1 bit to break
sentry routines; everything else was free!  This really put the pinch on
the Corp in the late game.  The problem was the elaborate setup, which
often took 7-8 turns to get working properly.  I also had Wilson and
a Bodyweight Data Creche so I was making many runs per turn.  With R&D
Interfaces and my Microtech AI Interface, I could run R&D 3 or 4 times
per turn at nearly no cost!  :-)

Just an observation.

