There is a little more finesse required, or a good player will
smear you on the pavement.  There are also lethal poison-pill
decks (Namatoki-Viral Test Site), Trap Decks (Trap!-Setup),
Unbeatable ICE decks (Ice Transmutation+Antiquated), Expense
Decks (Closed Accounts + Red Herrings).  All of these are viable
strategies that will shut down a host of deck types.  What makes
the game easy to win is when cheeseballs use the same predictable
decks, so the other side just needs to find a way to beat one deck
type.  Idiot clones that go out and make the same deck as clones
A, B, and C deserve to lose.  If everyone would gamble a little,
use some OTHER cards and stop trying for the "I'm the biggest
cheese-ball around award" then we could see what the game was like.

I guarnantee that I will stomp the hell out of the first misc.Joan
deck that gets in my face and I'm not using either of the two
"suggested" Corp deck types.

As to the Runner, I've never had a problem winning consistently,
with an occasional loss here and there to keep me humble.  I have
never, and will never, use the misc.Joan combo 'cause I think its
stupid and illegal.  (I own two of each of the required cards.)
"Somehow", my newest Runner deck has gone undefeated against 4 different
Corp decks, two tuned, two random, with very skilled opponents
at the helm.  As I said before, the game is healthy and in good shape.
The cards are losing their freshness, and I for one would like to see
Proteus hit the shelves ASAP; this doesn't mean that I've stopped
building new decks, however.  I never keep a deck for more than two
weeks.  If one works really well, I put it on paper in case I want
to resurrect it again at some point (Oh, say, for a tourny.).

> >all IMHO, I'm not trying to offend anyone. If you really have a great deck
> >without JOA/MFS, cool. I wouldn't mind making one w/o JOA/MFS cos' I would
> >like to see it banned :)
>
> Kinda.  If you ban the MFS/JoA combo (or just declare that it obviously
> doesn't work), the Speed Advancement decks will rule.  So, you gotta
> restrict the fast advancement cards.  But then, the Tag and Bag decks will
> rule.  I'm not sure what you can restrict to slow those decks down.

This is still not a problem.  First, it can be beaten.  Second, if
the people you play keep using the same deck because they're too
dumb to have fun, tell them they're assholes and stop playing with
them.  They will change, or they will not have anyone to play against.

> Anyway, my original predictions for the game are still on track.  The
> game has turned into a battle of degenerate and not-very-fun decks.
> In six months (five now) it will dwindle down to just the hard-core
> players with degenerate decks who can't find anyone (except other
> degenerate decks) to play (much like what happened to Star Trek,
> Star Wars, INWO, etc.).

I always have fun, even when playing a nob.  I don't think that many
card games are immune to this type of thinking, but since I don't
have to deal with it, I don't care.  I think most of us on the list
have tried a lot of different things, and we're still experimenting.
Some think they have the end-all decks for one side or the other,
but they WILL get beaten.  They just haven't found the right player
or the right deck to do the job.  I don't think anyone could predict
the outcome of a tourny with the players on this list as opponents.
We would see a lot of surprised faces, and we would hear a lot
of excuses, but the results would definitely be interesting.

I think you need to get a larger perspective Bill.  This is not M:TG,
Star Wars or Star Trek.  Keep in mind that most other games out there
have really BAD rules with really limited cards.  Netrunner is the first
game since Middle Earth that I think has a really good set of rules
and cards that remain fun.  This genre is evolving, and if the players
evolve with it the games will reamin exciting and cool.  If everyone
out there agreed with you, this game would suck for the reasons you gave;
this isn't happening anywhere but on the tourny cicuit, and those folks
are due to get slaughtered soon.  We're on to them, and we know how to
take them out...

Take a happy pill and get back to us.  :)

SeeYa,
Foolkiller
cwagner@cwo.com
