> > OK, Sparky, here you clearly states that with MFS you resolve the
> > trashing first, then gain bits. This should imply that if the
> > trashing is prevented, you gain no bits and the Joan/MFS combo
> > do not work. How can you then still say that the Joan/MFS combo
> > works?
>
> Do trashing first not resolve trashing first. So You 1)trash 2)get bits
> 3)then prevent trash.
>
> --
> Brian"SPOT"Dorricott                  \
> spotone@mindport.net                >{{}>
> http://www.mindport.net/~spotone      /

Brian, it doesn't matter *what* order you resolve them in!  It *clearly*
states on misc.for.sale: Gain 3 bits for each installed card TRASHED
this way.  If none of the cards go to the trash, then you don't gain
the bits!  Plain and simple...  If you let them go to the trash to gain
those bits however, then they certainly can't be prevented from being
trashed since they're already *in* the trash!!!  Too late to use JOA!
You can't use MFS and JOA in combo because it just doesn't work...

Saz
