Date:         Sun, 21 Jul 1996 13:28:06 PDT
Reply-To:     Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
Sender:       Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
From:         Bill Ingram <bing@ITS.BLDRDOC.GOV>
Subject:      Re: Loan from Chiba/MFS question

--- On Sun, 21 Jul 1996 00:09:08 +0100  Stephane Bura <bura@LAFORIA.IBP.FR> wrote:

>Look! I'm actually posting in this neverending thread!

Well, you know why this is a neverending thread, don't you?
It's because WotC has issued a ruling that is so far away from
reality that the average intelligent person can't understand
why and feels they have to post about it.

Remember the Maze of Ith/Serra Angel ruling?  WotC ruled that
the Maze would NOT stop the Angel.  The stream of folks complaining
that the ruling didn't make sense and that it contradicted every other
ruling, kept its thread going for six months.  Finally, WotC reversed
itself and the thread stopped dead in its tracks.

>This list is just a cool way to get fast answers to strange questions,

Or strange answers to fast questions.

WotC WILL change the ruling for the MFS/JoA.  Since every single person
who first hears of the ruling automatically disagrees with it, WotC
will eventually reverse their decision.  Even if they don't do it for
the "right" reason (i.e., the ruling doesn't make sense), they will have
to do it because the combo will be dominating tournament play.  We know
from their statements on MtG that they ban, restrict or change the rules
when a specific deck dominates play and no other deck can reliably stop it.
Sooner or later they will follow their stated policy.

-- Bill
