There is only *ONE* kind of meat damage! It's called... "MEAT DAMAGE". With
me so far? Meat damage which "cannot be prevented", cannot be prevented by
cards that "prevent all meat damage". Pretty simple how the English language
works, eh?

>This is not clear, never will be.  Best to say "just because" and go with
>the official ruling.  :)

It's quite clear to the vast majority of us, I'm afraid. When something says
it can't be prevented, it can't be prevented. What's so bloody difficult
about that?????

>p.s. Constructs really don't have any meat.  :)

Sure they do. Well, not "meat" per se, but there has to be some kind of
physical housing.
