From:         "LEONARD D. BLADO" <BLADOLE@HSDWL.UTC.COM>
Subject:      Virus Test Site

> You're wrong.  An installed card has to be rezzed to affect the runner, it's
> in the rules.

        Card Text supersedes the rules.  Virus Test Site plainly states
it does not have to be rezzed to affect the Runner.

> Not to mention 2 facts: 1) The rez cost of Virus Test Site is 0,

        So?  If they have a Speed Trap, I don't want to rez it.
Furthermore, future cards could have an impact on rezzing nodes.

> and 2) It can't have advancement counters on it when it's in R&D.

        This is true, but fundamentally irrelevant.  If the card text
states that you can have Virus Test State deal 2 Net Damage per
advancement counter while it is uninstalled (which it does), then
heck- if I somehow manage to get advancement counters on Virus Test
Site while it is in my R&D, then you'll be taking 2 Net Damage per
counter.

> The "even if not installed or rezzed" part of the card refers to the 1 Net
> Damage only.

        How do you figure?  Structurally, the commas used implicate that
the "even if not installed or rezzed" part is a clause applying to the
entire sentence- not just the latter part of the conjunction.

        Listening Sparky?  How about an official ruling?

        -Len Blado
