Date:         Mon, 22 Jul 1996 10:19:34 -0500
Reply-To:     Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
Sender:       Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
From:         Michael Gunderson <mikeg@MAIL.UTEXAS.EDU>

At 08:18 AM 7/22/96 -0400, Eli Tayrien wrote:
>Can I only put one advancement counter on an agenda every turn, and if not,
>how many actions does it take?

You can put as many advancement counters on an agenda every turn as you have
actions to do so, or cards that let you.  It takes one action and one bit to
put an advancement counter on an agenda, unless you've a card that lets you
do more with one action.

-MikeG
