Subject:      Re[2]: Loan from Chiba/MFS question

>It's like if you have a card that says "Take 2 brain damage and win the
>game" if you have a force shield in play. The 2 brain damages are not
>done as they are prevented but you still win the game, ok ?


>MOAH.

No it is not like that. To get the closest to MFS you'd have to have something
like this: Take any amount of brain damage you chose, win the game if you have
taken at least 2 brain damage.

And as with the ruling with Nanosurgeons, it would not work if you prevented the
damage.

