From:         Lohann <lohann@AZTEC.CO.ZA>
Subject:      How to enjoy the game!!!

>"Of course," you say, "degenerateness is a fact of life in MtG and almost
>every other CCG."  True.  But, it happened to NetRunner a lot faster than
>it happened to most other CCGs.  And, most folks claim that degenerate
>decks are actually the biggest problem with MtG and other CCGs.  It just
>seems frustrating that WotC would release a new game that is an obvious
>breeding pit for degenerateness.


OK OK OK I have read all this stuff about degenerate decks and how the game
ends up with certain cards and that is all. First of all, realise that the
game still has not got the complexity of MTG. Second of all realise that FUN
is the reason games exist. Here is what I do: Sure I collect RARE and
powerfull cards such as Access through Alpha etc. But I play the game for FUN.

Chuck ALOT of cards in a deck +/- 90 or so. (both sides) and play with what
comes up. EVEN BETTER have 14 AGENDA points as V conditions and now you are
talking FUN, STRATEGY etc.

PLay a group game, 2 runners and 2 corps (or any other combination) each
draws from the COMMON runner deck (120 +) cards and COMMON corp deck. See
the ganging up, the backstabbing etc.

There we go, listen: DONT PLAY TO WIN, PLAY TO ENJOY!!!!

btw: anybody got any other ideas for group games?
