Well, I usually use my amazing powers of mental domination to
get them to play fun decks, unless I'm specifically trying out a
new deck and want to give it a shakedown. The other tactic is to
play them once or twice, see what kind of deck they're using, then
ridicule them in front of their peers for playing such cheesy cards.

This usually works quite effectively, especially with the insecure
teenage male types that play around here. Man, laugh at them a
few times and they're either almost ready to cry or get violent! It
seems as though nobody understands what psychological
warfare entails in this context...

Actually, I don't normally do this, unless a person demands it by
being a weenie. Typically, the people I play don't try to play evil
decks; they just do the best they can with what they've got. If
it's politely requested that they play something else, and they
don't, we just start another game without them. Works for every
game!

Sean W. W. Harvey
Product Verification Specialist, Level III
Fulcrum Technologies, Inc.
Ottawa, ON

