Date:         Mon, 22 Jul 1996 15:58:37 -0100
Reply-To:     Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
Sender:       Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
From:         James Ludlow <ludlow@LAMBDATECH.COM>
Subject:      An actual use for Record Reconstructor (sort of)

OK, here's the situation.  Action 1, you run on R&D revealing an agenda and
the Bizarre Encryption Schemes that the Corp had installed on R&D.  No prob
right, you just run again and score it.  Unfortunately, you don't have the
bits to make it into R&D again.  Actions 2 and 3, you run with the Record
Reconstructor.  Do it again on action 4 if you think the Corp can draw more
than 4 on its turn.
Ta da, the agenda is yours.

BUT WAIT, there's more:
Let's say that the agenda above was one of the 6 Corporate Wars that is in
the Corp's deck.  On the Corp's turn, it uses its AI officer and mixes up
its R&D.  The top card just happens to become a Corporate War.  Then the
Corp draws, and installs the CW.  Then on its fourth action (which the Corp
has many ways of getting) it uses a fast processor card and scores the CW.
How in the world is the runner supposed to know whether or not the CW scored
was the same one that s/he accessed in the first place?

No this has never actually happened to me, but I'm pretty bored right now.

James Ludlow
ludlow@lambdatech.com
jdludlow@mtu.edu
