Date:         Mon, 22 Jul 1996 14:36:29 -0700
Reply-To:     Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
Sender:       Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
From:         David Orr <dmorr@SOFTWARE.NET>
Subject:      Re: NETRUNNER-L Digest - 21 Jul 1996 to 22 Jul 1996
In-Reply-To:  <2.2.32.19960722211052.00721b40@mail.westworld.com> from "Z" at
              Jul 22, 96 02:10:52 pm

> Why don't you read the Roving Submarine card again?  If I install a Chicago
> Branch, City Surveillance, or Blood Cat in a data fort, and then install a
> Sub right afterward, the fort can't be run, period.  How exactly did you
> plan to run on and trash it?

Well, the card says:

"Install only inside a subsidiary data fort. This fort may be run
 only if you installed or advanced a card inside or on this fort
 during your last turn. "

So since you installed something during that turn (The Roving
Submarine, for example), it can always be run the first turn that you
put it out.


HTH,
Dave

