From:         Stoneburne J SrA 51CS/SCUBS <stonebuj@CS51.OSAN.AF.MIL>
Subject:      Speed Trap vs. Setup

>Speed Trap
[Desc of Speed Trap]
>Setup!
[Desc of Setup!]
>The question: Must the runner take the damage or not?

Yep. Because the Speed Trap states that you have to use it immediately
after an ambush node was rezzed. If you pull it from HQ, or even R&D,
it will do the damage, because you can't (and don't need to, for this
card) rez cards in your hand.

>We decided he must take the damage. The Setup is not installed and it
>states, 'does 2 Net damage, even it is not installed'. I read this as, I
>need not to rez Setup to do the damage (and I can't rez a node in HQ too)=
>Speed Trap allows to jack out only after the Corp has rezzed that upgrade=
>Result: He cannot jack out and has to take the damage.

 Good for you.. and you're correct.

                         -James Stoneburner

