For most Runner's Short Circuit is a stable card, but seldom
needs frequent reminder visablity.   Chicago is a Corp Speed card
and often it's worth of ICE to protect it's fort.   I've stacked Banepi's
and then Jacked a Liche and it seemed that a 1 trash cost
was NOT worth the effort to make a run against it.

Advancing Agenda on a New SubFort in 2 actions is Standard.
Score/Bit-Gain nodes and then go for it!

6 Bits for a 4 Advancements -  Can you say Tycho.



