I've been following the discussions on this mailing list for some time
now, although I have had very little opportunity to play, and I've got a
couple of questions:

1)      It seems to me that people prefer playing with Succubus instead
        of Zetatech Memory Chip, and I'm wondering why that is. After
        all, if memory serves, they cost the same to install and provide
        the same extra memory. In my mind ZMC has two advantages: if it
        gets trashed, you don't lose any other programs; and you can
        install it even if you're currently using all available memory.
        The only advantage I see for Succubus is that I can bring it into
        hand with Short Circuit; does that outweigh the above?

2)      If a runner accesses Bizarre Encryption scheme and trashes it,
        does it still affect the agenda? I feel it shouldn't, in which
        case what it actually seems to do is make the runner run all
        over again to score the agenda. Am I interpreting this
        correctly?

Thanks for any help,

                                                A.J.
ajith@vcn.bc.ca
