>game(ie: Putting a large creature out, ect...), not having to watch if
>one was palming that Black Vise so he could put it out on the first
>turn.  Or watching one double pumping during the draw phase.

*WARNING:INCOMING FLAME*

Excuse me? I'm sorry, but I happen to LIVE in Richmond, Virginia,
and on average, we DO NOT CHEAT! I have played in very
enjoyable tournaments before, where I was beaten, soundly and
fairly. The opponents I played were very good sports about the
whole affair, and (since I was a new player at the time) even pointed
out to me exactly where the flaws in my deck appeared to be. So far,
their advice hasn't proven false.

Besides, you may note that this was an example of That Other
Game. That Other Game, on a whole, seems to be slightly more
competitive then Netrunner. Perhaps this is because in The Other
Game, lives are on the line, whereas Netrunner has more of a
playful feel to it (gee, I'm sorry I had to flatline that guy, but if he'd
just stayed out, he wouldn't have gotten hurt).

I must apologize to everyone who reads this (except, of course, for
the poster), but if you're going to say something bad about the
region in which a person lives, you can expect retribution.

*END FLAME*

Just my ? cents (the system can't really rate flames) on the issue,
-A.C.
