Yes, but if we take this into account, you couldn't use Microtech Backup
on a Startup Immolator, and new rules would also have to be implemented
similar to "burial" in magic. One of the things I like about Netrunner is
that you don't have to constantly keep track of which cards are killed,
and which are destroyed, or buried, or incinerated, or discarded, or
removed from the game, or kept seperate, or mutilated, or cornholed.
Everything is just TRASHED. (except of course for cards you remove from
the game permanently).

