getting into these *stupid* arguements.
No, he's not wrong. Let me show you why.

>An installed card has to be rezzed to affect the runner, it's
>in the rules. =20

You are correct! Congratulations for making it half way through the rule
book. Now, read the card. The card says "even if not istalled *or rezzed*".=
=20

Hmm. What a problem. Rules say "not unless it's rezzed". Card says "even if
not rezzed". Fortunately the rules also state that "whenever cards conflict
with the rules, the cards take precedence". (pg 32 of the rulebook)
So now the situation is resolved. Virus test site affects the runner fully,
even if it's not rezzed. Simple. (and please pardon my partial flame here...
I'm still ticked off about the ignorance and stupidity of another person in
another debate)

>Not to mention 2 facts: 1) The rez cost of Virus Test Site is
>0, and=20

Yes, but you'd still be rather silly to rez it. If you rez it, cards like
Speed Trap can be used.

>2) It can't have advancement counters on it when it's in R&D.

Very true. So what exactly is your point?

>The "even if not installed or rezzed" part of the card refers to the 1 Net
>Damage only. =20

No. The "even if not installed or rezzed" part refers to the entire card.
The "if it has no counters" part is the *only* part that refers only to the
1 net damage.
