From:         Patzer <med20095@THE_TRUTH_IS_OUT_THERE.WIZARDS.COM>
Subject:      Tycho Extension vs Political Overthrow.

Main thing about Tycho Extension is that it can be scored in 1 turn
through fast process. Even with 2 project consultants, you can't score
political overthrow in 1 turn. Also, after you score Political overthrow,
you still have to score another agenda.. lets say its a 3/1 agenda. The
cost of scoring 1 tycho and 1 4/3 (or 3/3) is much less than scoring the
9/6 and 3/1.

If a corp deck needs to score only 2 agenda, vs 4 agenda, the deck design
is quite different as for the former, a "short term view" can be taken
when designing decks. There is no need to think about "slugging it out" with
Runner in Phase III because phase III will never happen.

p.s. around here the atmosphere is pretty relaxed since most of us are
     magic refugees :), like in magic, as here, we have no problems with
     playing "fun" decks.

pps  playing NR has really got to me. My latest t2 deck is a library
     management deck with loads of deck manipulation cards :) I can
     beat the dreaded turbo stasis but I lose to Thallid decks...
