Date:         Tue, 23 Jul 1996 09:55:45 -0700
Reply-To:     Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
Sender:       Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
From:         Nick Svolos <Nick.Svolos@TRW.COM>
Subject:      Re: Enjoying the game

>PLay a group game, 2 runners and 2 corps (or any other combination) each
>draws from the COMMON runner deck (120 +) cards and COMMON corp deck. See
>the ganging up, the backstabbing etc.

>There we go, listen: DONT PLAY TO WIN, PLAY TO ENJOY!!!!

>btw: anybody got any other ideas for group games?

We had three players the other night and we ended up working out a system in which each player plays two games simultaneously.  For instance, Player A played Runner against B and Corp against C, B played Corp against C's Runner and so on.  All play was standard and turn sequencing was controlled by issuing a "token" to each game.  The player would take his turn and then pass the token to his opponent in that game.  After the game finished, we talleyed the score and reversed the direction.

While it doesn't sound like much, it was pretty interesting to try to keep track of two games at once, not to mention scout the other decks on the table, knowing you'd face them next.  At any rate, it sould keep folks from getting left out when you have an extra player with nothing to do

The Sik1
....who clearly doesn't have enough time on his hands.
