Date:         Tue, 23 Jul 1996 10:37:38 -0700
Reply-To:     Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
Sender:       Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
From:         "Marc \"Sparky\" Schmalz" <flatline@WIZARDS.COM>
Organization: Wizards of the Coast
Subject:      Re: Assorted Rulings

Stoneburne J SrA 51CS/SCUBS wrote:
> >3)If something does more than one net damage who picks the order
> >they hit the graveyard (important because of juckyard bbs)
>
>  When multiple cards of yours are hitting the trash (PuuuuLHEEEEZE don't say
> graveyard. :)  ), you get to choose the order. The owner of the cards always
> choose.

From the FAQ:
Q: If the Corporation trashes three of the Runner's hardware cards with Power
Grid Overload, who chooses the order in which they hit the Runner's trash
pile?
A: The Corporation chooses. Any effects caused by the trashing of those cards
(for example, the Runner's having to trash programs due to reduced MU after
memory chips have been trashed) are handled only after all those cards are
trashed.

Not from the FAQ:
If you take multiple points of damage, though, take the discards one-at-a-time
to randomly determine the order in which they hit the graveyard.

