Date:         Tue, 23 Jul 1996 13:48:20 -0600
Reply-To:     Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
Sender:       Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
From:         Richard Cripe <RCRIPE@SKADDEN.COM>

davidliu@VIOLET.BERKELEY.EDU writes:
>So... anyone have any good Roving Sub stories?  :)

Early in one game, we had 3 of our 4 pieces of agenda in HQ.
(2 Political Overthrows and a Corporate Retreat).  For safety,
we snuck an Overthrow on a Sub and waited awhile.  The
runner scored the other Overthrow but we got the Retreat.  A
little later we got our other retreat scored, so the only agenda
left was our PO on the Sub.  We had 3 more Project Consultants
left in the deck, so we weren't worried.  We collected bits,
toyed with the runner, and was generally smug with ourselves.
Eventually, we had plenty of bits and the two necessary
Consultants in HQ but we just sat and laughed at the runner's
feeble attempts to score the other point of agenda he needed.
Watching a frustrated runner bang his head against an R&D
with nothing he wants is very appealing.  We had nearly
exhausted our R&D prospects when the runner did something
unexpected.  He ran on R&D again and trashed one of our
multiple Whispering Campaigns.  Then he ran again and trashed
a Blood Cat we were trying to requisition.  To our horror, he
ran again, trashing the plans for our Remote Facility.  We looked
at R&D, knowing that there was only 1 card left.....The runner
saw this as well.  He ran again, nearly exhausting his bit pool
to make the final run.  Another Whispering Campagin showed
up and we glanced fearfully at the runner's available bits.....only
3 bits left....  So with a gleeful chuckle, we started our turn,
drew our last card from R&D, and scored our Political
Overthrow.

Final score:  Corp 12 agenda points, Runner 6.

Rick Cripe
rcripe@skadden.com
--These break-ins are unacceptable!
