> "...it does 2 Net damage per advancement counter on it (or 1 Net damage
> if it has no counters) even if it is not installed or rezzed."
> It does 2 Net damage per advancement counter on it even if it is not
> rezzed.
>
> If you can explain alternative interpretations, I'll try to write
> them up the way Bob, our Editor, might have written them.  Hopefully
> I can illustrate the differences.

I would credit the "alternative interpretations" to the following
posts...

*** Dated: 29-Apr-96 on NETRUNNER-L
Virus Test Site will do damage if the runner accesses it anywhere except
the achives.  If the runner pulls the card from the top of R&D, from HQ
or from a subsidary data fort before the corp has put any advancement
counters on it he will take 1 net damage.

In order to do more than 1 net damage the corporation needs to install
and advance the card.  The Test Site will do 2 net damage for every
advancement counter on it when the runner accesses it, but only if the
card has been rezzed.  If the corp does not rez the Test Site it will
still only do 1 net damage, no matter how many advancement counters are
on it when accessed.

Wendy
Merchant Relations
Wizards of the Coast

*** Dated: 29-Apr-96 on NETRUNNER-L
> Here's my question.  Say I've set up a Virus Test Site that's got 4 counters
> on it.  Runner says "Ooh, I'd better nab that agenda before he scores it."
> Muahaha.  He makes a successful run and accesses Virus Test Site.  Do I have
> to pay the rez cost to have the damage occur, or does it happen
> automagically when he accesses it?

Virus Test Site has a rez cost of zero, but yes, you do have to rez the
card in order to do the extra damage to the runner.  If you don't rez
the
card the runner only takes 1 net damage, not 8(2 for each of the
advancement counters).

Wendy
Merchant Relations
Wizards of the Coast

