Good points all around.  Unfortunately, the unoriginality is not what I'm
most concerned about.  What I'm concerned about are all of the losers out
there with the attitude of "If the rules don't SPECIFICALY say that I can't,
then I can."

I've ended up in fights before over such situations.  Netrunner was supposed
to have relatively airtight rules, but human nature has proved it wrong.

Could I put JOA/MFS in my runner deck if I wanted?  Yes, I could put TWO of
each in.  Do I?  No.  Why not?  Because it's illegal, and NOBODY will EVER
convince me otherwise.

