From:         "<Mark T. Tomczak>" <MacPrgmr@AOL.COM>
Subject:      Force shield-Lifesaver Nanosurgeons

On July 21, Zonker wrote:

>You know what I really have a problem with?  If the trashing can
>be prevented, but you still gain bits, why can't you prevent damage
>with a Force Shield and then use Lifesaver Nanosurgeons?  The
>whole argument for this lies in the following question, which was
>never answered when I presented it as a rebuttal last week:  Does a
>Force Shield AUTOMATICALLY prevent damage, or can you
>choose to let that damage pass through?  If you can choose to let it
>through, then you also have to choose to prevent it. Therefore, by
>the JOA/MFS illogic, this combo should work, too.  What, I didn't
>take damage?  Well, you didn't trash any programs!

>Either both have to be illegal, or both have to be legal.  You all
>know where I stand.

Sorry, Zonker, but from page 31 of the rulebook:
"If you prevent all damage from an effect that causes damage, you
are considered not to have been damaged at all by that effect."

Now, what I'm wondering is why didn't they extend that restriction
to ALL effects? Then JoA/MfS would not work. But they didn't.

Happy damage absorbtion and repulsion,
-A.C.
