Date:         Tue, 23 Jul 1996 14:14:25 -0700
Reply-To:     Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
Sender:       Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
From:         Joseph Ganis <jganis@IMVI.COM>
Organization: Dev-Com/IMV Internet (http://dev-com.com)
Subject:      Breaker pairs

Ok, today's topic is breaker pairs:

The definition is '2 breakers, that when available together in a deck,
should cover the spectrum of ice encountered so as to break them
efficiently.'

Example 1: Worm and Ramming piston.  Worm deals efficiently with walls
with strength <2, and Ramming piston deals with the rest of them.

Example 2: Black Deliah and Shakka. Black deals with expensive ice
(relatively cheaply), while Shakka deals with the lesser ice fairly
efficiently.

Other combos such as shakka/flak are also valid.  Which ones work well
for you?

-Joe
