Date:         Tue, 23 Jul 1996 14:50:58 -0700
Reply-To:     Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
Sender:       Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
From:         Z <zonker@WESTWORLD.COM>
Subject:      For Sparky!

>The next rules team meeting is on Wednesday.  I'd really like to have
>some information to share there....

We for the most part will agree with you that the combo has not affected
tournament play in the extreme.  What we ARE concerned with is a ruling on
whether such a combo was ever intended to be allowed.

Since it seems that you can choose whether or not to use a Force Shield,
choosing to use it to prevent damage is the same as choosing to use Joan to
prevent trashing.  Therefore, using Lifesaver Nanosurgeons after preventing
damage should work, if one is using the very same illogic that spawned JOA/MFS.

What we really want, instead of a specific ruling on a single combo, are
rulings on exactly how prevention works, EXACTLY why certain after-effects
of prevention are legal or illegal, and exactly what "trashing" refers to.
Is trashing similar to sacrifice, destruction, or burial from Magic, or does
it refer to something else entirely?  Thus far, trashing seems to be
anything anyone wants it to be, and that's wrong.

If the rules team can't resolve, or at least discuss important issues such
as these, there probably shouldn't be a rules team.  DO NOT take this to
mean that I think Proteus should go on the back burner.  Proteus should
certainly be #1.

-Z
