Date:         Wed, 24 Jul 1996 01:08:05 +0200
Reply-To:     Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
Sender:       Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
From:         Terje Braaten <terjebr@PVV.NTNU.NO>
Subject:      Re: Rule questions
In-Reply-To:  <31F53717.2CE6@mindport.net>

Brian Dorricott writes:
 > LEONARD D. BLADO wrote:
 > >         Yes, you can choose to break subroutines in any order.  However,
 > > no subroutines take effect until after you have "dealt" with all of
 > > the subroutines- either broken them, failed to break them, or not
 > > tried to break them, so it doesn't really matter.
 > >
 >
 > If I can choose to break the SR in any order why cant I break Jack
 > Attacks second routine first giving me a forced jack out at the end of
 > that "encounter" therefore preventing me from even needing to deal with
 > the second (first) (other) SR.
When you encounter a piece of ice ther is two phases:

  1. You break subroutines in any order you want, using any icebrakers
     you want.

  2. Any subroutines left unbroken happen to you in the order written
     on the card.

Hope this helps.

