=========================================================================
Date:         Tue, 23 Jul 1996 18:21:19 -0700
Reply-To:     Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
Sender:       Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
From:         Glenn Elliott <gee@WIZARDS.COM>
Subject:      Re: for Sparky!

zonker@westworld.com wrote:
>If the rules team can't resolve, or at least discuss important issues such
>as these, there probably shouldn't be a rules team.  DO NOT take this to
>mean that I think Proteus should go on the back burner.  Proteus should
>certainly be #1.

The rules team already *has* resolved the issue, you just don't like
the answer.  The current ruling is correct according to the current
rules no matter how many times you try to argue against it.  We will
not change the current ruling because it *is* correct according to
the current rules.

Arguing that the current ruling is wrong gets you nowhere.  In fact,
I'd have to say that it hurts your chances of being listened to in the
future.

Arguing for or against a particular wording change is fine, because
it helps us make sure that we *fix* the cards if we do decide to
reword them.  Pointing out wordings that are unclear or confusing
is also great - it helps us make the game better.

Saying that the rules team shouldn't exist is equally detrimental to
your reputation in our eyes.  Eventually we'll just stop reading your
posts because from our point of view there's no reason to answer
your questions.  You're not going to listen anyway, so why bother?

So... the rules team is considering alternate wordings for both of the
cards and the possible side effects of those new wordings.  If you want
to help, suggest alternate wordings and note the possible side effects
that they might have.  A couple of people have made suggestions, and
we have those cataloged.

We *might* change one or both of the cards which *might* make
the current ruling irrelevant.  *If* we change the cards, we may or
may not issue errata for the v1.0 versions of the cards.  If we do not
issue errata for them, however, they will continue to be played
according to the current ruling.

None of *us* are particularly thrilled that there is a degenerate
combo in Netrunner, either, but we're not going to go off willy-nilly
and change rules, rulings, and/or cards just to fix one combo.  WotC
has tried that before, and I think you're familiar with the results.

Glenn
