On Wed, 24 Jul 1996 07:45:00 JST, you wrote:

>Recently, Sparky so wisely stated:
>>"You may advance Virus Test Site before and after you rez it. When
>>Runner accesses Test Site, it does 2 Net damage per advancement
>>counter on it, or 1 Net damage if it has no counters, even if it
>>is not installed or rezzed. Ignore this effect if Runner accesses
>>it from the Archives. If Test Site is accessed from R&D, Runner
>>must show it to you."
>>
>>Read it this way:
>>"...it does 2 Net damage per advancement counter on it (or 1 Net damage
>>if it has no counters) even if it is not installed or rezzed."
>>
>>It does 2 Net damage per advancement counter on it even if it is not
>>rezzed.
>>
>>Did I answer the right question?
>>
>>If you can explain alternative interpretations, I'll try to write
>>them up the way Bob, our Editor, might have written them.  Hopefully
>>I can illustrate the differences.
>
> Huh! Well, that makes me look at the card in a completely different light.
>However, I have a question. Doesn't this basically make Speed Trap a
>useless card against ambush nodes, since most of them have that
>phrase on there?
>
>                         -James Stoneburner
>
>*We all work in a Roving Submarine.. ACK! Get out of my HEAD!*

Are you sure.I have all ambush cards and can not find on most of them
this phrase.Definetely I found it only on VTS.

On some cards you will find the phrase: ...even if not installed
(Trap!,...) but nothing about that you do not have to rez them to
effect the runner.So if such a card,like Trap!,is installed in a SDF
you have to rez it before the runner accesses it to effect him.
After the corp rez this card you can use Speed Trap to jack out.

If the runner accesses Trap! from R&d or HQ you can not use Speed Trap
of course,because you cannot rez cards in R&D or HQ.

Wart
