Subject:      Shields

Is the effect offered by a Shield/Force Shield/Whatever optional?

For example,  I am looking at the last card in my hand and wondering why
on earth I put the card into my deck in the first place.  I have
Lifesaver Nano-Surgeons installed as well as a Force Shield.  Can I
willingly take the next point of net damage I encounter, even when the
FS could prevent it, so that I can then use LN to get the cool cards
that I know must be around somewhere more quickly?

In effect, does the Runner call up the shield when needed, or is it an
active background program automatically preventing any damage it can?

