Date:         Wed, 24 Jul 1996 09:48:49 EST
Reply-To:     Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
Sender:       Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
From:         Slav Shuravesky
              <Slav_Shuravesky_at_Human__Resources@CCMAIL-METRO.PWCM.COM>
Subject:      Re[2]: Submarine Uplink vs. Jack Attack

>Submarine Uplink forces the Runner to try to jack out.  No, the
>card doesn't have the words "try to" on it, they are implied.  Jack
>Attack makes the result (in this case, successfully jacking out)
>impossible, so the Runner's attempt fails.
>
>Note that if Submarine Uplink was worded differently, Jack
>Attack would not prevent it from working.  If it said "Submarine
>Uplink jacks you out" then it would not be the Runner making
>the attempt and so Jack Attack would not prevent the attempt
>from succeeding.
>
>Glenn

Unfortunately I am not gifted with powers of telepathy and am unable to read the
minds of game designers for "implied" meanings. Why don't you just reword it to
state so explicitly, for stupid people like me.


Slav
