Date:         Wed, 24 Jul 1996 08:30:38 -0600
Reply-To:     Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
Sender:       Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
From:         Greg Dglas Teed <ac419@SFN.SASKATOON.SK.CA>
Subject:      Re: Rule questions
In-Reply-To:  <31F53717.2CE6@mindport.net>

On Tue, 23 Jul 1996, Brian "SPOT" Dorricott wrote:

> If I can choose to break the SR in any order why cant I break Jack
> Attacks second routine first giving me a forced jack out at the end of
> that "encounter" therefore preventing me from even needing to deal with
> the second (first) (other) SR.
> --
> Brian"SPOT"Dorricott                  \
> spotone@mindport.net                >{{}>
> http://www.mindport.net/~spotone      /

   If you are referring to Submarine Uplink, remember that it is not an
icebreaker and therefore cannot be used until after the first subroutine
affects the runner. In this case the "blanket prohibition" "cannot jack
out" takes precedence over "must jack out" according to the netrep.
   If you are referring to Dropp(TM), remember that Dropp(TM) uses the
phrase "end your run" as opposed to "jack out."  Using Dropp(TM) is *not*
jacking out and therefore Jack Attack's first SR does not prohibit its
effect.
   To the best of my knowledge, there are no icebreakers that require the
runner to "jack out."

- dglas (The Rational Fringe)

