In-Reply-To:  <Pine.HPP.3.91.960724033405.22642G-100000@starbase.spd.louisville.edu>

On Wed, 24 Jul 1996, Shadow Fang wrote:

>   Send me the JOA card and I'll put it in my deck, along with the
> misc.for-sale(I have that one), and I'll get back to you with the
> response.  :)  I have the Backup Drive and the misc.for-sale in my deck.
> I have the Back up Drive in case the corp decides to trash a much needed
> program.  I have the misc.for-sale in my deck for desperate bits.  I
> wouldn't actually trash needed programs, but I would trash programs in my
> Daemons, if I need bits more than the use of the programs.

   I tried using the JOA/MFS for the first time yesterday, in a fun game
of "Corporate War" (which is what we call "Keep it simple"). The costs in
actions to make the durn combo work are ridiculous. I got my Corp (I was
the runner) lotsa bits, but I ran thrice after the initial rush before the
game was was over and I was using Blink. Between the lengthy setup and the
costs in actions to reset (reinstall JOA; Junkyard the MFS), I don't see this
as a effective combo in one-on-one play. Let's not forget that in order to
Junkyard the MFS, you have to be really careful about drawing cards. The
discard comes after the runner has finished all actions. I will happily play
anyone who wants to use the combo against me; the game'll be over before
he/she gets the combo effectively set up and long before all dem bits can be
used...

   This ain't a Channel/Fireball situation, folks...

   Noone at my tournament in Saskatoon tried it. There was, however, the
beginnings of a positively *evil* ice destruction deck... *shudder*

