Date:         Wed, 24 Jul 1996 09:24:45 PDT
Reply-To:     Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
Sender:       Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
From:         Bill Ingram <bing@ITS.BLDRDOC.GOV>
Subject:      Re: Degenerate

--- On Tue, 23 Jul 1996 16:11:16 -0500  "Brian \"SPOT\" Dorricott" <spotone@MINDPORT.NET>
wrote:

>I have still yet to see a deck that will CONSISTANTLY win within 3 turns
>There is not a Degenerate deck in NR and I challange anyone to come up
>with one.

Well, obviously you can't.  In the case of the Runner, no matter how
good/degenerate your deck is, you simply cannot win in 3 turns if the
Corp has not shuffled 7 points of Agenda to the top quarter of his deck.

Similarly, when you play a Speed Corp deck, you could easily get a bad
shuffle (since you only start with 5 cards, it's very easy to get shafted
by a bad draw).  You won't be winning in 3 turns unless you get a very
good mix of Agendas (at least 7 points worth), Fast Advancements, and Ice.

A Tag 'n Bag deck should be able to do it within 3 turns...once.  The
second time a Runner plays against this deck, he'll probably take his
time to build up some defense against being Bagged before he runs.  Of
course, in a tournament situation, it'll be way too late to change your
tactics when your opponent moves on to the next round and you go home.

So, "winning in 3 turns" is an unreasonable test for degenerateness in
this game (actually, I can't think of any game where a player can build
a deck that CONSISTANTLY wins in 3 turns).  And, it also depends on what
you mean by "CONSISTANTLY".  99% of the time?  75%?  55%?

