Date:         Wed, 24 Jul 1996 09:16:03 -0700
Reply-To:     Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
Sender:       Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
From:         "Marc \"Sparky\" Schmalz" <flatline@WIZARDS.COM>
Organization: Wizards of the Coast
Subject:      Proteus Fact Sheet

Netrunner(R) -- Proteus(TM) Fact Sheet

o  Release Date:  September 3rd.
o  First limited edition expansion for Netrunner.
o  154 new cards in the set.
o  Booster packs contain mix of Runner and Corporation cards.
o  Booster pack MSRP:  $2.95(U.S.).
o  Flexible new ice and icebreaker cards that add a new
   dimension to the game strategy.  Runners and Corporations
   decide whether to pay the cost to make the ice/icebreaker
   a sentry, code gate, or wall.
o  Certain cards allow the Runner to give the Corporation
   "bad publicity," providing the Runner with another way to
   even the score against the corporation.
o  A new class of cards, "hidden resources," allow the Runner
   to use a tactic previously reserved for the Corp: playing
   cards face down and revealing their effect as a surprise move.
o  Cutting-edge artwork by world-renowned artist Moebius and
   popular Magic: The Gathering(R) artists.
o  Exciting online promotion of Netrunner with Wired
   magazine and HotWired: "Webrunner II: The Forbidden Code."
   This is the follow up to the highly successful "Webrunner: The
   Hidden Agenda."  Online August 16th through September 30th.

--
Marc Schmalz, aka Sparky!!    flatline@castle.wizards.com
Wizards of the Coast Customer Service Team
Netrunner FAQ and Main Page  - http://www.wizards.com/Netrunner
