>
> So, "winning in 3 turns" is an unreasonable test for degenerateness in
> this game (actually, I can't think of any game where a player can build
> a deck that CONSISTANTLY wins in 3 turns).  And, it also depends on what
> you mean by "CONSISTANTLY".  99% of the time?  75%?  55%?

In M:TOG if you can win in 3 turns 1 out of every 10 games it is
considered consistant and degenerate.

I consistantly win my OG in under 7 turns one out of every 4 games and I
am considered slow.

In NR I have rarely seen other than a lucky win anybody win in under 10
turns. I have never seen a game last longer than 23 turns (with the
possible exception of that submarine story about the political overthrow
deck) I have never heard of a corp losing by running out of cards. This
indicates to me that most games are between 7 to 25 turns in length the
possibility of scoring usable bits with JOA/MFS usually exists around
turn 14 or so this is which places it right in the middle of this
average (ok a little to the low side) this seems like a mildly pleasent
(for the runner) situation but hardly degenerate. Especially when as you
so eloquently put it the only turn 3 wins even remotely likely to be
consistant are CORP tag-n-slag decks. The only possible degenerate decks
seem to me to be these CORP types. Therefore if the runner has some toy
like JOA/MFS that has a possibity of exploiting a slow corp deck (like
most tag-n-slag are) it seems that it only counters out the degeneracy
of that deck. JOA/MFS is too slow to be of use against a speed processer
(baring a bad draw on the corps part) so if you base your deck around it
you will lose to some but beat others if you base your deck around speed
you will lose to t-n-s and beat the speed processors. Throwing in a MFS
just because it is a good card and might combo with your JOA in your
speed deck is not degenerate it is just using the cards to have a deck
that might be able to handle both types but now you have diluted the
original purpose of the deck. It is a no win situation you must try to
balance precariously and just PLAY THE DANG thing however it is built
the rules are well written with a few minor glitches this is not one of
them however and the Rules team RULES they have done a great job in
timely answering what few questions came up. and the fact that there are
so few questions (just the same ones repeated endlessly) is a testament
to the overall quality of this game.

To sum it up I dont think there are any degenerate combos in this game
there are some combos that if they come up really suck for one side or
the other (like trojan horse urban renewal and JOA/MFS) but both sides
have ways to handle it (like Fall guy and Chimera) So quit whinning and
start playing maybe you will find the one truly degenerate combo (the
one I will not share with anyone no matter what you try even if you send
me a wall of ice and Stephane Bura's  twin sisters home address)
--
Brian"SPOT"Dorricott                  \
spotone@mindport.net                >{{}>
http://www.mindport.net/~spotone      /
