Date:         Wed, 24 Jul 1996 11:51:19 -0700
Reply-To:     Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
Sender:       Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
From:         "Marc \"Sparky\" Schmalz" <flatline@WIZARDS.COM>
Organization: Wizards of the Coast
Subject:      Official Card Errata

Here are your answers:

All of these changes will take place in v2.0.  Treat them as errata to
your v1.0 cards.

misc.for-sale will read "successfully trashed" instead of "trashed."
You can no longer get the bits for misc.for-sale if you use Joan of Arc.

Lifesaver Nanosurgeons will read "successfully damaged" instead of
"damaged."  This makes Lifesaver Nanosurgeons read better - the way it
has always worked.

Submarine Uplink will read "ends your run" instead of "forces you to
jack out."  This ends the ambiguity over its interaction with Jack
Attack.



FYI:  I have over 100 unread messages from Netrunner-L.  I'm going to
delete any messages with subjects dealing with these cards, since I
think I've just answered all your concerns.  If you have an issue you
feel is unanswered, please re-post it or mail it directly to me at
'flatline.'

Thanks for understanding.

Oh, for those of you who did the BattleTech flavor text contest, the
winners' list is up, including their winning entries.  Check out:
http://www.wizards.com/BattleTech/Welcome.html

--
Marc Schmalz, aka Sparky!!    flatline@castle.wizards.com
Wizards of the Coast Customer Service Team
Netrunner FAQ and Main Page  - http://www.wizards.com/Netrunner
