From:         MOAH <moah@MICRONET.FR>
Subject:      Don't make it so you play with the wording on the card, please.
In-Reply-To:  <01I7G0UHX1HU0066CL@utrcgw.utc.com>

>Glenn wrote:
>> We *might* change one or both of the cards which *might* make
>> the current ruling irrelevant.  *If* we change the cards, we may or
>> may not issue errata for the v1.0 versions of the cards.  If we do not
>> issue errata for them, however, they will continue to be played
>> according to the current ruling.

>        Well, I'd like to voice a request that you institute a general
>policy of "most current wording" on cards- that is, whether or not
>specifically stated, the latest version of a card has the official
>wording and errata applied to it, and all older versions must follow
>it.  It ends up being a LOT simpler in the long run, and avoids much
>confusion as people try and figure out what errata applies to what
>versions of a card (more to the point, it ensures all cards function
>in a consistent manner).

I would like to back up Len here, because having seen what it gives
on Magic: The Other Game, i don't want THAT to happen to netrunner.
It seems pure logic to me that only one wording for a given card
applies, whatever the version of the card. Please, make it so the
latest wording/errata issued is the only one in use, for the fun of
the game and the rest of the traders. I don't like the idea of a
MFS v1.0 having a demesurate value, while v2.0 will be snorted at.

In advance, thanks to the rules team for taking this into consideration.

>        -Len Blado

MOAH, full time turnip.
