From:         "<Mark T. Tomczak>" <MacPrgmr@AOL.COM>
Subject:      Crash Everett/Microtech Backup Drive

On July 23, dglas wrote:

>Here's a neat one I encountered recently. A runner
>(using a Blink/Dropp deck) used Crash Everett to draw
>two from his stack. He then kept one and put the second
>card (a program) into his Microtech Backup Drive
>instead of the trash. Whaddaya know...Crash sez
>"trash."

*Bzzzt* Wrong! Sorry, but this combo won't work
(although it was a good idea). Microtech says: "Whenever
one or more installed programs are being sent to the trash at the
same time..." The cards were drawn, not installed, so they go to the
trash (unless he returns them to the stack).

My 2 Bits,
-A.C.
