From:         Mike Foster <mfoster1@VOYAGER.NET>
Subject:      Re: Enjoying the game

At 09:52 PM 7/23/96 +0100, you wrote:
>>We had three players the other night and we ended up working out a system
>>in which each player plays two games simultaneously.  For instance, Player
>>A played Runner against B and Corp against C, B played Corp against C's
>>Runner and so on.  All play was standard and turn sequencing was
>>controlled by issuing a "token" to each game.  The player would take his
>>turn and then pass the token to his opponent in that game.

My suggestion for better turn sequencing... All runners go simultaneously.
When all runners are finished, all corps go simultaneously. Speeds the game
up, avoids some complications, and generally works *very* well with 4 or
6-player team games. Should work here as well.

