Date:         Wed, 24 Jul 1996 17:49:40 -0700
Reply-To:     Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
Sender:       Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
From:         Foolkiller <cwagner@CWO.COM>
Subject:      Re: Early traps slowing down the runner

I don't want to see our friend Mitch get flatlined, so:

Mitch Williams wrote:
>
>   Can you say 'Diplomatic Immunity'(sp) ?  If you install this early then
> the corps tag -n- whatever cards are almost useless untill he scores that
> first (usually expensive) agenda.  By this time you can have your other
> defenses set up.
>
> Just my X Bits worth. (Assign X any value you like).
>
> Mitch A. Williams
> mitchw@tyrell.net

Think so?  OK.  Turn 1 you play Diplomatic Immunity.  Action 4 you
run my HQ and see a piece of ICE.  Corp's turn:

Action 1: Accounts Receiveable = tagged!
Action 2: Trash a resource; hmmmm, how about Diplomatic Immunity!?
Action 3: Urban Renewal.  Boom!  Runner fall down and go splat.

Resources are the worst way to stop Tag'n'Bag because the Corp
can remove them so easily.  You need to avoid the tag in the
first place, with a combination of a good link (see the opinions
floating around out there right now) and a Nasuko Cycle, just
in case the Corp whips out a Trojan Horse.

Until a card is made that "locks" a resource into play, D.I.
is just a false sense of security.  Too bad, really.

Hardware is a much safer way to protect your hide (not including
the Emergency Self-Construct program).  Armored Fridge, Full Body
Conversion, Dermatech Body Plating, and Nasuko Cycle are all good
pieces of hardware that the Corp will have a hard time removing
and which make flatlining the Runner a chore.

Don't forget the Chrome, baby!  This is the world of Cyberpunk!
Metal and flesh made one, man and machine.  Gotta love it.

SeeYa,
Foolkiller
cwagner@cwo.com
