Date:         Wed, 24 Jul 1996 18:10:30 -0700
Reply-To:     Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
Sender:       Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
From:         Foolkiller <cwagner@CWO.COM>
Subject:      Re: Bizzare Encryption Scheme

Greg Dglas Teed wrote:
>
> On Tue, 23 Jul 1996, MOAH wrote:
>
> > Well, a question i have already asked and got no answer to is:
> > If the runner leaves the BES in the node and runs again, is he
> > affected or not ? on the card it reads "this does not affect
> > further run" and i had always read that for when the cards is
> > trashed, but a friend of mine argued with me and said it was no
> > further run, even if it's not trashed...
> >
> > So, anyone ?
>
>    Well, if noone else will, then I'll give it a try... :)
>    It *seems* clear to me that as long as the BES is being accessed its
> ability is in effect (first line). Therefore the last line may only be of
> interest if the BES has been trashed previously. If the runner accesses the
> fort a second time after trashing the BES on the first run, then the
> agenda is liberated. If, however, the BES is still in play, then it is
> accessed again and the agenda is not liberated.
>
>     Other interpretations? Comments? Derisions? Deleted expletives?

Hey guys.

We do not play it that way here.  If I run a subsidiary fort and
the Corp rezzes a BES, (assuming there is an agenda in the fort)
then I end the run without scoring the Agenda.  I (for whatever
reason) choose not to trash BES during the first run.

The card says "This does not affect any further runs."  If I run
again immediately, BES does not affect me.  We take it to mean
that BES does not affect any further runs against the SAME agenda,
whether BES was trashed or not.  The BES does not stipulate that
the card does not affect further runs IF trashed.

If this is correct (Sparky?), then I would like to suggest that
v2.0 clarify the wording in the last phrase to something like this:

"This does not affect any further attempts to score that agenda this
turn."

Anyone else?

SeeYa,
Foolkiller
cwagner@cwo.com
