From:         Stephane Bura <bura@LAFORIA.IBP.FR>
Subject:      Re: Several Replies

Len wrote:
>        Much as I hate to disagree with the downtrodden souls who have
>yet to acquire a Wall of Ice (hell... if you're that desperate I'll
>send you one- I've got like 7 of the useless things), look at CNC:
>
>Corporate Negotiating Center     0 3 Node-Asset
>     At the start of each of your turns, gain 1* for each 'agendaœ card stored
>     in HQ that you show to Runner.
>
>        Since you have have multiple "start of turn" effects, you can
>simply keep showing the 'Runner Agendas in your hand to gain bits with
>multiple CNC's out (just as if you multiple Braindance Campaign out,
>you would get to use them all).  BTW: Another reason to love CNC is
>the fact that it has a rez cost of 0 and a trash cost of 3...

You know what? There's nothing like bribery to convince me.

CNC is cumulative!
I've seen the truth.

Ok. Now another question:

Where is it written in the rulebook that the corp mandatory draw
comes before "start of turn" effects.
It is written that this draw "start your turn", but is it a start of
turn event, that is must the corp draw before using the effects or
can it choose to use some effects and then draw?

I think it's the later, but it's late and I'm tired.
I just taught NR to two friends of mine and we had a blast with
untuned starters. Damn, this game is good.
(Sorry Moah, it was totally unexpected)

