Date:         Thu, 25 Jul 1996 03:54:31 +0100
Reply-To:     Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
Sender:       Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
From:         Stephane Bura <bura@LAFORIA.IBP.FR>
Subject:      Re: Running Flow Chart

Comments from a compulsive programmer:

>10) Runner: Pay to break subroutine
>    Did you break the subroutine?
>         Yes: Are there any other subroutines you want to attempt to
>         break?
>              Yes: Go to 7

"Go to 8" would be more appropriate.

>12) Runner: Pass the ice
>
>13) Runner: Special card effects can be used.  Also, choose to end or
>    continue run

A bit confusing. It could be:

12) Runner: Pass the ice. Runner & Corp: Special card effects can be used.
[some effects must be used while the runner passes the ice.]

13) Runner:  Choose to end or continue run

(other Corp special effects are accounted for in 2)


>16) Runner: Choose the order in which you want to access the cards
>    there, including face-down cards.
>
>17) Corp: Cards affect Runner in the order he or she chose.  Any
>    face-down cards are revealed.

Are these really two different steps or can the runner choose the next
card after having dealt with the previous' effects?
I thought it was the later.

Altogether, a neat flow chart (but bear in mind that I love these things ;)

