I'm very good at guessing bits with SE.
I trained myself by playing Douglas Hofstadter's mind games (published
in Mathemagical Themas). In one of those, you can undermine the
other players bet by betting just below his bet but, otherwise, it's
the player with the highest bet who wins.
It does wonders for your synaps.

And after that, you'll feel curiouser and curiouser when playing SE ;)


