Date:         Thu, 25 Jul 1996 06:45:51 -0600
Reply-To:     Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
Sender:       Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
From:         Richard Cripe <RCRIPE@SKADDEN.COM>
Subject:      Social Engineering -Reply

Foolkiller wrote:
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
[stuff about revealing bits spent with Social Engineering
and the trouble of counting remaining bits in pool removed]

In friendly games, you're right that this is no problem.
However, in tournament, I have a large problem with anyone
putting their hands underneath the table for any reason
whatsoever.  (too easy to do sleight of hand).  I suggest (and
usually insist when I don't know my opponent in tournament)
that rather than holding the number of bits, that the person
write down on paper what the number is.  It seems the only
safe way to do this.  This goes as well for link/trace attempts.

-----------------
>On a related note, if the Runner chooses an unrezzed piece of
>ICE to pass after successfully using Social Engineering, can the
>Corp still rez the ICE as the Runner passes?  I think so, 'cause
>the Runner still approaches the ICE before passing it, and that
>is
>when we rez the ICE.

I believe you're correct.  Looking at Inside Job, if the corp
couldn't rez anything before the runner "automatically passes"
a piece of ice, the runner would be able to breeze by a whole
fort of unrezzed ice.

My 2 bits worth
Rick Cripe
