Date:         Thu, 25 Jul 1996 09:32:43 -0700
Reply-To:     Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
Sender:       Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
From:         "Marc \"Sparky\" Schmalz" <flatline@WIZARDS.COM>
Organization: Wizards of the Coast
Subject:      Sneak Preview
Comments: cc: Stephane Bura <bura@laforia.ibp.fr>

Stephane Bura wrote:

> Sneak Preview states that you get the card back in your hand at
> the end of your turn. As the runner can choose the order of the
> end of turn events, can he get his card after his discard phase and
> thus have more cards than his hand size would allow during the
> corp's turn?

"At the end of the turn, take the program into your hand."

Unline Magic, there's no 'phase' in which you check hand size.  As
far as I know, you just cannot end your turn with more cards than
allowed by your maximum hand size.  Discarding isn't an 'end of turn
effect' so it doesn't fit into timing.  It's just the last thing you
do during your turn.  Check for a discard after all those 'end of
turn' effects.

Actually, I wish Magic worked like that.... :^)

--
Marc Schmalz, aka Sparky!!    flatline@castle.wizards.com
Wizards of the Coast Customer Service Team
Netrunner FAQ and Main Page  - http://www.wizards.com/Netrunner
