Date:         Thu, 25 Jul 1996 11:47:03 -0600
Reply-To:     Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
Sender:       Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
From:         Richard Cripe <RCRIPE@SKADDEN.COM>
Subject:      Re: no more MFS... my corp deck now invincible? -Reply

Len wrote:
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
>I was
>wondering, is there anyone out there who is playing a solid
>deck that
>ISN'T primarily a JOA/BMI blitz deck?
>        -Len Blado
<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<
I've got an ice destruction deck that is vicious and usually only
loses to someone playing heavy tag and bag.  I can usually see
it coming and prepare for it, but sometimes they get me before
I can save my butt.

It eats speed processing corp decks alive.

I agree that the BMI/JOA/NGF is really common and boring.  My
corp deck usually makes people pay a lot for running with this
one.  Against speed weenie ice, sure it's fine, but when you're
running up against Haunting Inq, Cindy, Lich, Shotgun Wire,
etc, it gets expensive fast.

My friend has a Shell Traders deck that gets ridiculous(ly) fast.

Another deck I had that worked about half the time was my
Quest for Catekin deck.  When I got the fifth action within the
first few turns, then the deck started to hum.  By the time I
was at 7 actions, I pretty much had it wrapped up.  The main
trouble with it was when I couldn't roll a six to save my life
(literally).  Most actions I had a turn was around 12-15, I forget.

My advice to people who want to build solid decks without
BMI/JOA/NGF:  degeneracy.  Don't limit yourself to 4 cards of
a single type.  Go wild.  It really helps.  I'm not talking about
20 Scores in a deck.  20 Inside Jobs is another matter....  A
friend of mine is working on a deck with more than 5 Code
Viral Cache.  (ewww.....)  You'd be surprised what it's like
to always have what your deck needs in your hand.

Oh, and always have a fair chunk of meat damage prevention/
tag avoidance.  It's a dangerous Net out there....

Rick Cripe
rcripe@skadden.com
--These break-ins are unacceptable!
