Date:         Thu, 25 Jul 1996 15:53:14 -0400
Reply-To:     Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
Sender:       Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
From:         Brian Bankler <bankler@RTP.ERICSSON.SE>
Subject:      Randomly choosing for Social Engineering...

        Is not a good idea. If I suspect that the runner is choosing randomly,
I simply state the number of bits he has as my (corp) guess. Why? Because
it is the most damaging. It's true I'll only guess right 1/n-2 of the time,
but I always get maximum advantage when I do guess right.
        If we play a psych game (with equal skill) I'll guess right 1/n-2
of the time with an expectation of getting rid of half of your bits. I've
effectively doubled the expectancy when I win.
        Of course, if you re-roll (or whatever) whenever you roll the maximum
number, then you aren't playing a pure random strategy....and we are back
to a psych game.

        For a game that that a lot of people claim has a random strategy,
but allows clever players to take advantage of random strategies, I suggest
6 nimmt! (Which was published in English as 6 Takes! I think. The cow card
game).
