Date:         Thu, 25 Jul 1996 15:37:21 -0700
Reply-To:     Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
Sender:       Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
From:         "Marc \"Sparky\" Schmalz" <flatline@WIZARDS.COM>
Organization: Wizards of the Coast
Subject:      Virus Test Site Update

Regardless of what I might have said in the past, the rest of R&D
has supported my last interpretation of the Virus Test Site wording.
If I said otherwise in the past, I have to apologize.  I'm human, too.

As a group, we don't like the fact that it operates differently than
the other Ambush cards.  Wednesday, we'll discuss what we want to do
about that for v2.0, if anything.

Again, I'm sorry if I've given contradictory rulings, especially if I
gave them to you through Wendy.  I usually give Wendy the hard rules
info even when I'm away, so it's all my fault, not hers.

Anyway, the more I work with Bob and the others, the more I understand
the way they write the cards.  That's probably the root of the switch.

For those of you who missed it, this is the Rules Team's interpretation
of the card "Virus Test Site":

--

"You may advance Virus Test Site before and after you rez it. When
Runner accesses Test Site, it does 2 Net damage per advancement
counter on it, or 1 Net damage if it has no counters, even if it
is not installed or rezzed. Ignore this effect if Runner accesses
it from the Archives. If Test Site is accessed from R&D, Runner
must show it to you."

Read it this way:
"...it does 2 Net damage per advancement counter on it (or 1 Net damage
if it has no counters) even if it is not installed or rezzed."

It does 2 Net damage per advancement counter on it even if it is not
rezzed.

--

Marc Schmalz, aka Sparky!!    flatline@castle.wizards.com
