Date:         Thu, 25 Jul 1996 16:14:40 -0700
Reply-To:     Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
Sender:       Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
From:         "Marc \"Sparky\" Schmalz" <flatline@WIZARDS.COM>
Organization: Wizards of the Coast
Subject:      Re: Shields

Philip Harvey G-Net 701 3371 wrote:

> Is the effect offered by a Shield/Force Shield/Whatever optional?

Force Shield reads:
"Prevents up to 2 Net and/or brain damage total each turn."

This means that you can choose to have it prevent 0 damage when you are
damaged by an effect.  Now if the card had read, "Prevents 2 Net and/or
brain damage total each turn" you would automatically have the first two
points of damage you receive preevented, no choice.  The 'up to' gives
you the choice.

Dermatech Bodyplating, Green Knight Surge Buffers, Raven Microcyb Eagle, and
Techtronica Utility Suit should all say "up to 1" as well.  This change will
be made in v2.0, and you can treat it as errata now.  You'll still be playing
it the way everyone does intuitively :^)

--
