Subject:      Re: Bizzare Encryption Scheme

>    Well, if noone else will, then I'll give it a try... :)
>    It *seems* clear to me that as long as the BES is being accessed its
> ability is in effect (first line). Therefore the last line may only be of
> interest if the BES has been trashed previously. If the runner accesses the
> fort a second time after trashing the BES on the first run, then the
> agenda is liberated. If, however, the BES is still in play, then it is
> accessed again and the agenda is not liberated.

Right.  If you re-access BES on a second run, the whole card text takes
effect and you can't score the agenda.  If you trashed BES on the first run,
it won't affect further runs.

