From:         "Tod T. Fox" <vulpine@MV.MV.COM>
Subject:      Intro and a tactic

Hiya,

I'm Tod Fox... I've been playing NetRunner for a while now, I think its a
kickass game, and I've been doing my damndest to recruit everyone I can.
I live in the Monodnock region of southern New Hampshire, so I'd be happy
to get together with any players in that area or in the Brattleboro, VT area.

Here's a tactic that the people I play with have started using:

hide your bits.  A starter deck box works good for this, just put your
bit counters behind it.  The opponent quickly loses track of how many
bits you have, and then won't be able to know ahead of time if you can
rez that Mastiff/afford that run.

