The Corp has the right to count your bits before you start the effect, but
once you've started the guessing game he's out of luck.  You can do exactly
what is mentioned above.

>On a related note, if the Runner chooses an unrezzed piece of
>ICE to pass after successfully using Social Engineering, can the
>Corp still rez the ICE as the Runner passes?  I think so, 'cause
>the Runner still approaches the ICE before passing it, and that is
>when we rez the ICE.

The pertinent part of the card reads:
"Then make a run on that fort, during which you automatically pass
that piece of ice."

Remember my little flow chart from yesterday?  My interpretation is that
this card forces the Runner to go straight from #1 to #12 for the first piece of
ice without passing the stuff in the middle  The stuff in the middle (step #3,
actually) is where you get to rez ice.

1)  Runner: Declare your run
[...]
12) Runner: Pass the ice

