Thrill me with your acumen, Clarice.

1. The amount you post has very little to do with your ability to play
Netrunner.

2. The amount that you do post has very little to do with your ability
to play Netunner.

For all you know I could be some guy who knows nothing about Netrunner
but is spouting off things he heard from his friends.  On the other
hand, I could be Richard Garfield using an alias and choosing not
to add anything because I don't feel like it.

Now, if you go out spouting off something someone thinks is stupid,
that person has a right to flame you, regardless of how much they know
about the game, as long as they back up why what you said was stupid.

And I don't care if you're Einstein (or really Berkeley (sp?), if you
do psychology/philosophy) .  If you tell me that I'm just a figment
of your imagination, I'm still going to call you stupid, despite the
fact that I know just about nothing about philosophy.

