Marc Schmalz writes:
 > >On a related note, if the Runner chooses an unrezzed piece of
 > >ICE to pass after successfully using Social Engineering, can the
 > >Corp still rez the ICE as the Runner passes?  I think so, 'cause
 > >the Runner still approaches the ICE before passing it, and that is
 > >when we rez the ICE.
 >
 > The pertinent part of the card reads:
 > "Then make a run on that fort, during which you automatically pass
 > that piece of ice."
 >
 > Remember my little flow chart from yesterday?  My interpretation is that
 > this card forces the Runner to go straight from #1 to #12 for the first piece of
 > ice without passing the stuff in the middle  The stuff in the middle (step #3,
 > actually) is where you get to rez ice.
Did you have this question in mind when you made the flow chart? I
doubt it. An other sign of this being a hasty decision is that going
from #1 to #12 is not what you by any means do. The runner may f.ex.
choose to automaticly pass ice no. 4 at the datafort. He then first
encounters ice 1,2 and 3 (if they are rezzed or the corp chooses to
rez them) and then "automaticly pass" ice no. 4.

It is clear from your flow chart that you have passed the ice in #12
but where are you considered to start passing it?
Both #5 and #2 seem to be logical.
Sparky seems to choose #2.
Why not choose #5?

Well, I guess I got to leave this to R&D.

