The number of bits in your bit pool, the number of cards you
have in your hand and the contents of Trash and Archives is
not hidden knowledge. Both players may ask for that
information at any time.

I wonder, though, if you must tell the following to your opponent:

- The number of cards (left) in your deck;
- The number of cards you cut with AI Interface.

It could be important if the corp has a good memory and I just want
to cut a random number of cards after he's used Planning Consultants.

I know that in friendly play, you should give this information, but
what about competition?

