Date:         Fri, 26 Jul 1996 08:06:59 -0400
Reply-To:     Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
Sender:       Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
From:         "LEONARD D. BLADO" <BLADOLE@HSDWL.UTC.COM>
Subject:      Re: cards from HQ

> The first is probably an in-house type of answer. If a runner runs on HQ =
> and accesses a card. Puts it back because he cant trash/score it. Can =
> the Corp now shuffle his HQ ?
> The reason i ask is that i am fed up making 2+ runs on teh HQ and =
> drawing the same card. How do you guys handle this ???

        HQ is supposed to be hidden- there is no rule requiring the Corp
to keep the cards in HQ in any particular order.  Yes, it's frustrating
to keep on running HQ and get the same card over and over again, but
that's life.  If you want to get around this problem, you can play with
cards such as Executive Wiretaps (increase chance of accessing that
Agenda), Gremlins, and Romp through HQ.
        In my mind, the main reason to access HQ anyway is to play
sabotages, so I rarely worry about this...

> Second, Proteus. I have been thinking about the bad publicity rule, is =
> this going to make agenda's harder to score. ie. i have two bad =
> publicicty counter, my agenda's will cost two extra points to score.
> Will teh corp get bad publicity counters for playing evil agenda's like =
> corpwar and political overthrow or will they be given by runners? If the =
> runner runs a fort and steals a "bad" agenda shows it to WNS who =
> publically shame the corp.
> (unless the corp is WNS who keeps it quite, tags the runner and urban =
> renewals him :*) )

        Hmmm... this brings up a good point.  Supposedly Proteus is going
to hit the streets on September 3rd.  Is this the most unadvertised
expansion set of all time or what?  I haven't seen ANY mention of Proteus
except from Sparky & co- no full page ads (like when Netrunner came out),
no "oh, boy Proteus is coming" mentions in various magazines, whatever.
Is this some fantasy that Sparky dreamed up, or did they just forget to
tell the WotC Marketing department about this?

