Date:         Fri, 26 Jul 1996 20:14:31 +0800
Reply-To:     Patzer <med20095@the_truth_is_out_there.WIZARDS.COM>
Sender:       Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
From:         Patzer <med20095@THE_TRUTH_IS_OUT_THERE.WIZARDS.COM>
Subject:      Immovable object meets irresistible force?

Hi,
someone posted (Foolkiller?) that he had a runner deck that hasn't lost
yet. I'm never going to play in any US tourneys anyway, so if you would
like to try vs my corp in irc (without R&D files-unplayable), you're
welcome to. Currently unbeaten by non JOA/MFS. Lost narrowly twice to
JOA/MFS (one of them was to my deck) - both of us had scored 2 agenda
each, and it was pure luck of the draw who scored the next. Its quite
often 10-0.

I beat a "cycle through the scores!" [I've no idea how many he had] deck
today only 10-2 because I made a stoopid mistake.. he played social
engineering and had 10 bits left, he needed 8 bits to break the other ice
on the fort. I just had to guess "2" in order to prevent the run. Instead
I guessed "3" and he only had 2 in his hand (all the ice was unrezzed and
concealed), so he got thru' aargh!

Stephane: (yeah, he's famous enough to merit personal attention)
I'm using cascade in my runner deck too, almost 90% of the time corp
declares he's forgoing 3 action once there're 2 counters - almost a
timewalk :)

NR boosters dropped to about us$2.10 today (IA & 4th ed was already $1.95)
that should attract an even larger pool of NR players and enhance card
availability.. yahoo :)
