>--
>Stephane Bura                                              bura@laforia.ibp.fr
>I could put something in French here if I wanted to.

Speaking of AI Interface. Lets say you are running with AI Interface and R&D
Files.  You use R&D Files and find 2 agendas clumped together. You only have one
run left this turn. If you cut down to the first agenda and score it, your
opponent draws the second one into his heavily protected HQ. Instead, you can
cut down to the second agenda and score it. Then as your first action next turn
you cut corp's entire deck except for the last card (which is the first agenda
that you viewed with R&D Files) and score that one as well.

Slav
