Date:         Fri, 26 Jul 1996 10:51:59 -0700
Reply-To:     Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
Sender:       Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
From:         "Marc \"Sparky\" Schmalz" <flatline@WIZARDS.COM>
Organization: Wizards of the Coast
Subject:      Social Engineering

Sorry about any confusion - I have a real answer now.

You must encounter a piece of ice before you pass it.  This means
that the Corporation has a chance to rez the ice before it is passed.
On the flow chart, it looks like this:

1)  Runner: Declare your run
    Is there any ice?
         Yes: Go to step 2
         No:  Go to step 13

2)  Runner: Approaches outermost unpassed piece of ice.  Special card
    effects can be used.

3)  Corp: Special card effects can be used, including rezzing nodes,
    upgrades, and the piece of ice being approached.
    Is the piece of ice being approached already rezzed?
         Yes: Go to step 6
         No:  Go to step 4

4)  Corp: Decide whether or not to rez ice
    Do you want to rez the ice?
         Yes: Go to step 5
         No:  Go to step 12

5)  Corp: Turns ice face-up (if it has not already revealed) and pays
    the rez cost in bits.  Ice is now rezzed.

6)  Runner: Encounter ice

At this point, if a special card tells you to automatically pass a piece
of ice, you skip straight to:

12) Runner: Pass the ice

If you think that this is a common-enough occurance, I can plug an
option into #6, which would read:
   "Does an effect cause the Runner automatically pass this ice?
         Yes: Go to 12
         No:  Go to 7"

--
Marc Schmalz, aka Sparky!!    flatline@castle.wizards.com
Wizards of the Coast Customer Service Team
Netrunner FAQ and Main Page  - http://www.wizards.com/Netrunner
