>>For this sort of thing (usually this is what we do for traces), we have
>>some dice handy.  Rather than using bits, we hide the dice behind our
>>cards and pick our amounts.  With a d6, the six is usually used to
>>represent zero bits.  Multiple dice will allow you to choose six or
>>more bits.
>
>>That way it doesn't matter what bits are in sight.  It's my
>>understanding that players have the right to know how many bits are
>>in their opponent's bit pool.
>
>>Skipper Pickle
>>spickle@ili.com

