From:         Stephane Bura <bura@LAFORIA.IBP.FR>
Subject:      Re: Rules questions

>*Can you liberate discarded agendas?

That's the main point of running on the archives (except if
you know the secret trick about Record Reconstructor ;)
Yes, you score all the agendas that you find there.

>*Where do agendas go when you score them?  How about nodes, where do they go
>when  you rez them?

The nodes stay where they are while the agendas go somewhere
on the table where you can see them, but they're out of the game.

>*Am i correct in assuming that it takes one action and one bit to put an
>advancement counter on an agenda?

You are correct (assuming you don't use a card effect).

>*Did i send this to the right address?

I'm afraid not.
Therefore, you didn't recieve this answer either.

