Date:         Fri, 26 Jul 1996 14:43:59 -0600
Reply-To:     Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
Sender:       Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
From:         Greg Dglas Teed <ac419@SFN.SASKATOON.SK.CA>
Subject:      Re: Rules questions
In-Reply-To:  <199607261737.NAA14437@cyber1.servtech.com>

On Fri, 26 Jul 1996, Eli Tayrien wrote:

> *Can you liberate discarded agendas?  I made a run on my friends archives,
> and there were a couple agendas in the face down pile.  I said that,
> according to the manual, i should put everyting in the face down pile into
> the face up pile, and then access everything in the face up pile.  Should i
> score those agendas?

   Yes; archived (discarded) agenda are fair game.
   Corps *score* agenda. Runners *liberate* agenda.

> *Where do agendas go when you score them?  How about nodes, where do they go
> when  you rez them?

   Scored or liberated agenda are set aside and counted toward the seven
point victory condition. Any special abilities of *scored* agenda can be
used by the Corp provided the conditions for doing so exist and the Corp
can meet the costs of using them.

> *Am i correct in assuming that it takes one action and one bit to put an
> advancement counter on an agenda?

   Yes. It takes one action and one bit to put one advancement counter on
any advanceable card, including agenda.

> *Did i send this to the right address?

   Yep. Welcome aboard. :)

- dglas (...a branch of the welcome committee...)

