Date:         Fri, 26 Jul 1996 17:53:02 -0500
Reply-To:     Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
Sender:       Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
From:         "Brian \"SPOT\" Dorricott" <spotone@MINDPORT.NET>
Organization: SPOTone Services
Subject:      Re: JOA/MFS Ruling

Shadow Fang wrote:
>
>   I was just wondering how come that I didn't get the original post?  I
> got several peoples response to it, but not the original.
>
>   I also have been trying not to recieve my posts and the acknowledgement
> post, but the commands that I use aren't working.  I did go back to the
> "rules" about posting and sending commands.  I copied the commands
> directly from the "rules" and they didn't work.  I tried the "help"
> command.  Hell, that didn't "help" at all.  Any ideas?
>
>   Thanks.

When your mail gets sent to you it goes through at least 2 different
computer systems. The one the sender calls Host and the one you call
Host. In between it can go through any number of other systems this
routing sometimes is very confusing (try sending a message to
billgates@microsoft.col (misspelling is intentional) the message will
not get through but you will recieve a message telling you all the
places it tried to go.) Anyway sometimes this routing will cause two
messages sent from the same host to the same person to be delivered in
much different speeds this is caused by the traffic pattern at that
time. (basically some of your mail is caught in a submarine uplink)
relax be patient eventually it will all come.

This page spell checked by NOBODY.
--
Brian"SPOT"Dorricott                  \
spotone@mindport.net                >{{}>
http://www.mindport.net/~spotone      /
