Date:         Fri, 26 Jul 1996 18:13:39 -0400
Reply-To:     Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
Sender:       Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
From:         Jeff Stolt <JStolt1@AOL.COM>
Subject:      Crash Everett...

My favorite "useful-card-to-play-with-Crash-Everett" is Junkyard BBS.

I rarely play without both of these cards, so it's not like I built my deck
around this combo, but it IS rather nice to know that the card that I decide
to Trash with Crash Everett can be picked up right away with Junkyard BBS.
  In fact, I always Trash the second card that I pick with Crash Everett.
That way, I keep cycling through my deck. The only time I ever DON'T Trash
the card is if I need more cards in my hand, and I'm drawing twice in a row.
Then, I can be assured of getting the best 2-out-of-3 cards in my hand, with
the 3rd sitting on the top of my Trash if I want it.

Anyway, I know that it's not the most efficient, or coolest combo, but I've
gotten quite used to the "luxury" it provides. <G>

I don't know about anybody else, but after about the third time I use Mantis
to get a card from the deck [and Junkyard BBS to recycle Mantis], I start
feeling guilty...<G> I might as well play with my Stack face-up, and play
with only two actions per turn...picking whatever card I want instead of
using Mantis/JYBBS. I start feeling guilty because my deck isn't random
anymore. Sure, I have to spend 4 bits & 2 actions to get a card, but there's
no more suspense. I no longer have to worry about getting the right card.
  In fact, I almost took Mantis out of my deck, but without it, I am usually
at a horrible disadvantage until I get the right cards out. (i.e. JYBBS,
icebreakers, etc.)
=========================================================================
