Subject:      Re: Accessing Agenda (timing)

Chris Patterson wrote:
>
> > From: Zack Weintraub <gandalf@fast.net>
> > Subject: Re: Accessing Agenda (timing)
> >
> > a namatoki plaza.  The VTS has flatline the runner, and agenda to let him
> win.
> > He runs in and access the two cards.  Does he:
>
> He loses the game, since damage is inflicted before scoring the agenda.
>
> Chris Patterson
> cmp@ix.netcom.com

I believe the Runner wins the game s/he has scored (accesing the cards
in the order he/she decides) the agenda and gets the 7th point game ends
here. Take these quotes from the rules book.

"Immediately" means before any other action is taken in the game.

If multiple events take place at the same time, the player whose turn it
is
chooses the order of those events.
