Date:         Fri, 26 Jul 1996 16:13:14 -0700
Reply-To:     Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
Sender:       Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
From:         Z <zonker@WESTWORLD.COM>
Subject:      Re: NETRUNNER-L Digest - 25 Jul 1996 to 26 Jul 1996

>If I were the referee, I wouldn't consider that cheating.  That's simply
>doing some research.

It's cheating.  The player obviously did not have enough experience,
knowledge of the game, and/or skill to win.  The research should have been
done beforehand.  I ask you this: You're taking a final exam. You don't know
the answer. You decide to sneak out to look up the answer in your textbook.
Are you cheating?

Same goes for CCG's. If you take advantage of the ability of Microtech AI
Interface, it's cheating. There must be some method of making sure that
Trap!, Setup!, and Virus Test Site are actually acknowledged by the runner,
without resorting to turning cards 90 or 180 degrees, and without needing 1
referee for every 2 players in every tournament, which would be an ungodly
expense.

-Z
