Date:         Sat, 27 Jul 1996 01:23:43 GMT
Reply-To:     Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
Sender:       Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
From:         ARTNER Wolfgang <wartner@VIP.AT>
Subject:      Re: Speed Trap vs. Virus Test Site
In-Reply-To:  <199607262050.NAA19868@dfw-ix2.ix.netcom.com>

On Fri, 26 Jul 1996 15:50:07 -0500, you wrote:

>I guess I missed the final say on how Speed Trap can be used when running a
>data fort containing either a Virus Test Site, a Setup! or a TRAP! card.
>Could somebody please clarify how this card works with these three cards.
>The confusion lies in the fact that Speed Trap can only be used after a
>corporation rezzes a node or upgrade. Since these cards are not usually
>rezzed by the corporation, Speed Trap would pretty much be useless against
>them.
>
>Well?
>
>Chris Patterson
>cmp@ix.netcom.com

The final ruling for Virus Test Site says that this card must not be
rezzed to effect the runner ( card text:...even if not installed or
rezzed ). So if you access VTS in a SDF Speed Trap! is useless,because
there is no need for the Corp to rez the card.

On Setup! and Trap! you just find the phrase:...even if not
installed.Nothing about not rezzed.So these cards must be rezzed to
effect the runner,when he accesses them in a SDF.So you can use Speed
Trap for this two cards.

If you access VTS,Setup! or Trap! in R&D or HQ,Speed Trap is useless
too.

wart
