Date:         Fri, 26 Jul 1996 21:52:42 -0700
Reply-To:     Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
Sender:       Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
From:         Foolkiller <cwagner@CWO.COM>
Subject:      Short Fiction

The Militech corporate security center was quiet this evening.
A half-eaten pizza and a dozen empty soda cans lay strewn around
the circular table.  The circular room's walls were covered with
monitors, each reflecting various sites in and out of the Net.
The darkness was punctuated by the phophorus glow of the screens
and the digital readouts from the massive array of hardware.

Dieter's seat was empty at the moment, and his monitor belied
the truth about security perimeter seven.  The Mastiff software
set up to ward off intruders appeared to be running fine, but
appearances can be deceiving...

"Dreff, hand me that back-up disk the southern office flew in
today.  And get your goddamn soda off my magazine."

"Screw you Jenny.  Here's your stupid disk."

"Where the hell did Dieter go?  Didn't he say he was just going
out for a smoke.  Chester's out sick, and Esslin is a screw up.
How did I get hooked up with you wanna-be's?"

--------
The chill night air penetrated Dieter's thin coat.  He took
another drag from his cigarete, blowing the smoke from his
nostrils.  He watched the guards patroling the gate one hundred
meters away, illuminated by huge sweeping lights.

He finished his smoke and flicked away the butt.  The silent
bullet slammed through his skull as the cig hit the ground.
Steam rushed up from the tiny hole.

Two silent figures slipped away toward the system relay station.

--------
"Oh shit!"  Jenny started up and quickly dashed to Dieter's seat.
An alarm began sounding and a red lamp switched on inside the tiny
room."

"Someone just entered the third ICE in sector seven.  That's R&D!"

"Christ, Dreff, if anyone gets in there it'll be our ass!"

A panicked look washed over Dreff's face as he scrambled for the
hardcopy of the Mastiff program.  Jenny struggled to get the
crashed data wall in the second line of defences back in operation
but an Immolator routine had already destroyed most of the code.

Dreff slid the CD into the loading station.  He slipped a jack into
his temple and his eyes glazed over as he became reconstructed in
Net-space.

--------
As the crystalline form of the intruding Runner leaped and ran
across the virtual minefield the third ICE formation began
to rez.  The slight graphic interference diturbed the sharp
images as the new program integrated itself into the virtual
world of the Net.  The ground erupted as several lethal Data
Darts shot into the air.  Their code quickly found the Runner's
signal and they began their attack run against him.  The first
Dart impacted the Runner and sent a lethal pulse of energy
towards his mind.  The deck's surge buffers absorbed the shock,
but they burned out in the process.  Two more Darts struck the
Runner's humanoid icon, blasting his cortex with sharp bursts
of directed energy.  Then the backlash hit him.  As he stumbled
into the data storage nodes of R&D a final surge of power cut
the Runner's access to his stored programs, preventing him from
breaking any further ICE.  No matter, he was almost there...

--------
"I see you, you little fuck.  You're in for a little surprise,
prescribed by your Doctor!"  Dreff hit the activation button
on his terminal, and the Mastiff program rezzed inside R&D...

--------
The Runner's icon quickly began scavenging through virtual file
folders, looking for the plans for the Corporate relocation.
His new "girlfriend" told him the files were here, and all he
had to do was find them.

The growl behind him had a tin sound, like a metal dog snarling
through a blown out speaker.  He turned ready to fight and saw the
massive black and blue neon hound, towering above his own icon.
The roof of the construct had derezzed to allow the program to fit
inside.  The spiked collar blazed electronically.  Then the pearl
white teeth began to gleam against the dark background.

The Mastiff snapped at the Runner's tiny icon.  He raised a hand to
enable his Krash program but it fizzled in a spurt of disassociated
electrons.  The jaws of the killer ICE locked into his signal and
sent the initial pulse of damage through the Net.  Then it fired
its most lethal electronic poison which coursed through fiber-optic
cables straight back into the shocked boy's head.

His body convulsed violently in his father's chair.  The jolt forced
his head backwards sharply, yanking the jack cables from his temple.
The life monitor light on the temple plug switched from green to red.
His brain sent a flatline signal to the monitor and it began to
emit its high pitched distress signal.

His mother cried out from downstairs...

---------
<The next day..>

"Find out who leaked the information.  I suspect that new temp
in R&D has something to do with it.  Find her and see if she knew
the boy."

The dark man in the pressed suit turned towards the bitter killer
sitting across his desk.  The solo wore a long army green trench
coat with 22 dog-tags hanging from the left shoulder.  Dirty clothes
and long dread-locked hair portrayed him as a street bum, but the
outfit allowed him to get into the street crowd.  His arsenal
of weapons bulged beneath the coat.  A scar ran the length of his
worn and rugged face, crossing the right eye, which now glowed with
a hideous red light.  Two days growth covered his jaw, which now
let a small smile break the hardened image.

"And if she did..."

"The usual.  I'll give you your standard fee even though she's not
a physical threat.  This intrusion has made me very angry."

Foolkiller stood up and turned.  He walked silently out of the
office, with a bounty on the head of a young girl working for
Edgerunner Temps...

THE END?


Hope you enjoyed!

SeeYa,
Foolkiller
cwagner@cwo.com
