> Well we have had our netrunner music debate how about films.
> Runner/corp films that i can think of a the moment are
>
> Max-Headroom. - Cool English film
> Hackers - Hollywood's answer to the hacker generation
> Wargames        - Do you want to play a game ?
>
> Anybody have any other suggestions as i have probably missed the important ones.


um, lemee see,

Sneakers, although not really cyberpunk, or wholy dedicated to computers,
had some neat cracking stuff, and the idea of breaking into corporations,

Freejack (Mick Jagger of the stones, and someone else, Emilio Estevs
perhaps) in a very cyberpunk future


and some additional Netrunner trivia:

the name Wilson (weeflerunner apprentice) comes from the Gibson book,
Count Zero. The original Wilson (can't remember his last name) was
described as a total fuck-up. The main character refered to himself as a
wilson whenever he made a mistake. There are several good "runner"
stories in "burning Chrome", a compilation of Gibson's short stories. The
best (imho) is the title story, Burning Chrome.

Alex
