From:         Chris Patterson <cmp@IX.NETCOM.COM>
Subject:      Re: Accessing Agenda (timing)

> From: Brian "SPOT" Dorricott <spotone@MINDPORT.NET>
> Subject: Re: Accessing Agenda (timing)

> > > a namatoki plaza.  The VTS has flatline the runner, and agenda to let
him
> > win.
> > > He runs in and access the two cards.  Does he:
> >
> > He loses the game, since damage is inflicted before scoring the agenda.
> >
> > Chris Patterson
>
> I believe the Runner wins the game s/he has scored (accesing the cards
> in the order he/she decides) the agenda and gets the 7th point game ends
> here. Take these quotes from the rules book.

I quote the Sparky runner flowchart and the way the game is played around
here:

17) Corp: Cards affect the runner in the order he or she chose.
18) Runner: liberate any agenda and trash anything you can.

Since Virus Test Site and others are dealt with in 17, the runner would
flatline before reaching 18.

Regards,

Chris
