deck, with a ton of R&D Interfaces. My favorite (and arguably the best) is
the breakerless deck, centered around Inside Job/Social Engineering/Security
Code WORM Chip/Core Command Jettison ICE. Other decks I've had were the
general-purpose deck (my C-64 deck) and the poor-man's runner deck (nearly
everything with an install cost of 0 or 1; no bit gainers except ESM,
Databroker, and Luciderne) which was actually quite a bit better than I
expected it to be...
