From:         Mike Foster <mfoster1@VOYAGER.NET>
Subject:      Re: Rules questions

At 01:37 PM 7/26/96 -0400, you wrote:
>*Can you liberate discarded agendas?

Yes.
>
>*Where do agendas go when you score them?

Set them aside. They can no longer be run on by the runner, nor do they take
up space in a SFD.

>How about nodes, where do they go
>when  you rez them?

Nowhere. They stay right where they are.

>*Am i correct in assuming that it takes one action and one bit to put an
>advancement counter on an agenda?

Unless a card permits you to do something else, yes.

>*Did i send this to the right address?

No, but we'll gladly say "yes" and "no" to your questions, even though we
have no idea what you're talking about...

