> Date:    Fri, 26 Jul 1996 17:26:55 MST
> From:    Steve Bauer x1014 <sbauer@ERNIE.GEG.MOT.COM>
> Subject: Re: Restrictive Net Zoning
>
> >Date:    Thu, 25 Jul 1996 16:13:13 -0800
> >From:    Frisco Del Rosario <Frisco_Del_Rosario@CATTEKIN.VIP.BEST.COM>
> >Subject: Suffocating from Restrictive Net Zoning
> >
> >I've having difficulty with a mean opponent who carries about 10
> >Restrictive Net Zonings, and usually manages to play two on RD on his first
> >turn, then proceed with his Cascade-me-to-death plan.
> >
> >I hate to think that the guy has a good idea. :) How should he be stopped?
> >
> >Frisco_Del_Rosario@cattekin.vip.best.com
> >"Beaver damming the informathion thuperhighway thinthe 1994."
>
> Restrictive Net Zoning doesn't really hurt you, it just slows you down.
>
> For it to work the runner has to focus on one data fort.  This ussual
> means he is using other cards that focus on one data fort(in your
> case Cascade) Take advantage of this.  You can place agendas in forts with
> a lot less protection than you would normally feel comfortable knowing that
> all things being equal the runner will opt to run R&D.
>
> Restrictive Net zoning is purely a bit penalty.  Good bit gainers can help
> you overcome it, and a runner to focused on putting cascade counters
> on you will be less likely to go after your bit gainers (and if they do
> you have achieved your objective any way).
>
> Don't waste actions trashing Cascade counters when you only have a few and
> almost never trash them if there is a resnoable chance the runner can run
> you again the next round.  It would take a huge amount of cascade counters to actual make you lose the game.  The most important thing is to either score enough
> agendas to win or keep the runner out of R&D.
>
> If the runner throws two(or even one) restrictive net zoning on you early
> in the game don't assume it is a luck draw.  Place as much ice as you can
> afford on the restricted zone.  Odds are if he drew two of anything on the
> first round he has much more than two in his deck.
>
> Of course this advice is rather general, I would need more information
> on exactly what your oppponents deck is doing to give you the best way to
> beat it.  What is he using for ice breakers?  bit earners?  link?
>
> -- Wired

Greetings folks. Just got on this list yesterday, and spotted this. Most
likely, I'm the mean opponent Frisco's referring too. :) I'm still
working on the deck, mainly cause I'm only now learning how to run, and
still don't have a really big clue. The main strategy of my deck is to
put about 4 cascade counters out, and generally make a nuisance of myself
until they trash an agenda. I've got 8 RNZ's in my deck, so I usually put
3-4 on R&D, and the rest on HQ or the Archives. A couple inside jobs,
Bartmoss with Patel's Virus, and I usually do pretty good. The deck is
pretty weak against tag and bag right now, but I haven't faced many of
those yet so I'm still clueless as to what to add/take out. Anyway,
here's the current version of the deck. If anybody has any tips, I'd
appreciate them. My big decisions right now are do I use Bartmoss, or go
with a cracker for each ice type. And, how to fit in more RNZs and Inside
Jobs. I won quite a few games putting 3 RNZs on R&D in the first turn,
then Inside Job/Junkyard BBS on through.

Here's the deck:

8 Restrictive Net Zonings (Trying to fit 2 or 3 more)
2 Zetatech Software Installers (I hate paying for Bartmoss if it goes away)
1 Force Shield (Might add 1, dunno yet)
1 Dropp (Keep the Corp poor earlygame, and see what it's got late game)
1 Joan of Arc (Keeps Bartmoss around)
1 Afreet (will morph into a Succubus when I get another)
2 Succubi
1 Newsgroup Filter (Bits 'n Bits 'n Bits)
1 Bartmoss
1 Mouse (Hmm, is that gonna hurt, or make me happy?)
1 Cascade (Nice and annoying, might go with Gremlins/Shredder instead)
1 Pattel's Virus (Goes good with Bartmoss. Heh, your ice is -8)
1 Forged Activation Orders (Use it or lose it you sellyourmotherformoney
                            Corp *^%%**&%$$)
1 Access to Arasaka (Link)
1 Access through Alpha (Big link)
1 Inside Job (How about a deck with 15 RNZs, and 15 Inside Jobs)
1 Nasuko Cycle
6 Livewire's Contact
1 Quest for Cattekin (OUCH!!! That's the 5th 1 in a row!)
1 Silicon Saloon Franchise (bit or a card, bit or a card, hey! I don't
                            have to worry now)
4 Jack 'n Joe (Now where's those RNZs---Might swap 1 for N.E.T.O)
3 Mantis
1 Militech MRAM Chip (ever have 3 of these out, and STILL have a handsize
                      of 2?)
3 MIT West Tiers (Might drop the Jack 'n Joes cause of these)
1 Junkyard BBS (Trash it, or Smash hit?)
1 Shell Traders (Leftover from when I had AI Boon in this thing)
1 Short Circuit
1 Arasaka Owns You (I Gotta Rock? I got something for you too pally!)
1 Total Genetic Retrofit (Is this thing really as cool as it looks?)
1 Tycho Mem Chip
Total = 51 cards
