Subject:      Re: NETRUNNER-L Digest - 26 Jul 1996 to 27 Jul 1996

>I guess I missed the final say on how Speed Trap can be used when running a
>data fort containing either a Virus Test Site, a Setup! or a TRAP! card.
>Could somebody please clarify how this card works with these three cards.
>The confusion lies in the fact that Speed Trap can only be used after a
>corporation rezzes a node or upgrade. Since these cards are not usually
>rezzed by the corporation, Speed Trap would pretty much be useless against
>them.
>

Virus Test Site is immune to Speed Trap, but I'm not sure about Setup and
Trap, because neither contain the words "or rezzed."

Of course, it is my personal opinion that Trap and Setup cards are best used
to protect HQ and R&D.  Installing them in subsidiary forts is bad strategy.
Much better to use a Virus Test Site in this situation, even if Setup and
Trap were immune to Speed Trap.

-Z
=========================================================================
Date:         Sat, 27 Jul 1996 13:52:03 -0700
Reply-To:     Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
Sender:       Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
From:         Z <zonker@WESTWORLD.COM>
Subject:      Re: NETRUNNER-L Digest - 26 Jul 1996 to 27 Jul 1996

>He, "in response," paid to remove
>the remaining shell counters and installed the card. I have doubts about
>the legality of this.

Hell no he can't.  Netrunner has FIFO timing, which is to say, completely
the opposite of Magic.  Your friend has Magic-itis, and can't accept not
being able to respond with an interrupt.

Anyway, as soon as it's gone, it's gone.  For example, if you played
something that trashed a resource and gave a tag, and then you decided to
trash a Wilson, he couldn't respond by trashing the Wilson to avoid the tag.
He'd have to get another copy out before he could take the counters off.

-Z
