From:         Patzer <med20095@THE_TRUTH_IS_OUT_THERE.WIZARDS.COM>
Subject:      Tons of R&D Interfaces?

Well, I personally can't stand hardware. Especially when theres a better
software out there. R&D interface costs 4 to install vs. R&D protocol
files which cost 0 and takes up 1 MU. I can't seem to be able to bring
myself to pay 4 for a interface... it seems so... expensive. HQ interface
is probably a bit better cos' there's no good s/w available. Expert
Schedule Analyzer? Maybe.

Of course, my aversion to hardware may be due to the fact that I have
only 2 shell traders (lying around gathering dust next to my roving
submarines :)). Once I get 5, maybe I can build that kind of deck.

I don't know about the other runners, but I'm constantly short on bits
(even though my first priority is to install newsgroup filter). Maybe
its all those black ice so many people are playing with. I think only 2
players have anonymous tips which is the main reason. [oh yeah, my corp
deck doesn't take advantage of lack of anonymous tips amongst players -
its has 4 black ice out of 16/17 ice only]. Whereas I've encountered
players who play with multiple mastiffs & liches & other black ice...
Once I get my hands on an anonymous tip, they'll think again. Muahahaha.

Patzer.
