Sender:       Netrunner Discussion List <NETRUNNER-L@ORACLE.WIZARDS.COM>
From:         Zack Weintraub <gandalf@FAST.NET>
Subject:      Re: Crash Everit

In a fit of madness, Jeff Stolt wrote:

> My favorite "useful-card-to-play-with-Crash-Everett" is Junkyard BBS.
>
> I rarely play without both of these cards, so it's not like I built my deck
> around this combo, but it IS rather nice to know that the card that I decide
> to Trash with Crash Everett can be picked up right away with Junkyard BBS.
>   In fact, I always Trash the second card that I pick with Crash Everett.
> That way, I keep cycling through my deck. The only time I ever DON'T Trash
> the card is if I need more cards in my hand, and I'm drawing twice in a row.
> Then, I can be assured of getting the best 2-out-of-3 cards in my hand, with
> the 3rd sitting on the top of my Trash if I want it.

Question: Why do you trash the card with Crash Everett, just so you can take it
back from your library, instead of putting it on top of your library and taking
and action (as opposed to an action an a bit) to do the same thing, with the added
benefit that you see the next card on top of your library, and can take or trash
that. <Phew> That was a long sentence.

---Zack (if anyone understands me, I'm happy)

