Subject:      Re: Cascade Counters

Steve Bauer wrote:
> Don't waste actions trashing Cascade counters when you only have a few and
> almost never trash them if there is a resnoable chance the runner can run
> you again the next round.  It would take a huge amount of cascade counters
> to actual make you lose the game. The most important thing is to either score
> enough agendas to win or keep the runner out of R&D.

This can be a fatal mistake.  Though it may take a while to "deck" the corp,
the cards that are dropped in archives could be agendas, and I NEVER like having
to protect archives.  Also, I saw a game the corp let Skivviss counters grow
to seven.  He was happy his hand was alwaysed replenished, but wasn't so happy
when there were 2 cards in his R+D

